- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Horn clause verification, which is a topic in logic and automated reasoning. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of abstract interpretation and automata in program verification. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is relevant as the paper introduces interpolant tree automata and their application in verification. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is possible as the paper deals with software verification, which is a topic in software engineering. 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with symbolic manipulation of Horn clauses.
